Transport CAS Chris Obure's driver was shot dead on Wednesday night at the civil servants' quarters in Kariobangi South, Nairobi. Evans Omondi had parked his car at about 9 pm when a lone gunman accosted and shot him in the chest at close range. The motive is unclear as nothing was stolen from him; his phone, wallet and other personal effects were found at the scene. Nairobi DCI boss Ireri Kamwende said investigations were on and that updates will be given. Click here for the latest political news   